<section class="px-6 py-24">
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-6 text-[var(--ctp-subtext1)]">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--ctp-text)]">About</h2>
    <p>
      <strong class="text-[var(--ctp-text)]">sev</strong> is not a feature-complete Emacs clone,
      but aims to be genuinely usable, lightweight, portable, and highly configurable via Scheme —
      filling the same role as Lua in Neovim or Elisp in Emacs.
    </p>
    <p>
      The ultimate goal is a foundation for <em>non-text-editor</em> applications where text
      editing needs to be a first-class capability: music composition environments, wiki-like
      tools, collaborative editors, and more.
    </p>
    <p>
      Built with <a href="https://libsdl.org/" class="text-[var(--ctp-blue)] hover:underline">SDL3</a>,
      <a href="https://www.nicbarker.com/clay" class="text-[var(--ctp-blue)] hover:underline">Clay</a>,
      and <a href="https://synthcode.com/wiki/chibi-scheme" class="text-[var(--ctp-blue)] hover:underline">Chibi Scheme</a>.
      Targets Linux, macOS, Windows, and WebAssembly via Emscripten.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
